So I'm very excited to be here.

86
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Thank you for having me.

87
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,000
It's an honor.

88
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Thank you so much, Jesse.

89
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,000
And welcome.

90
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Welcome to Brazil.

91
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,000
I know it's your first time here in my country.

92
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,000
So welcome.

93
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:06,000
I hope that your stay does justice to you, not only as a journalist, but also as a guest.

94
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:15,000
What was the first time, if you can recall, that you started to take UFOs more seriously?

95
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Was there a moment, do you remember, when you first heard about UFOs?

96
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Yes, in my youth, there was this huge curiosity about these phenomena, and it was a type of healthy curiosity, because the news was divided between phenomena that were observed, and there was also sci-fi literature that used this subject matter as the object of writers, journalists, and also aficionados.

97
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:52,000
So it got all of our attention, and we saw that in the movies, in literature, and yeah, it got my attention.

98
00:08:52,000 --> 00:09:05,000
I've never monitored it really closely, but I've always been curious about seeing it in the news, especially with regards to phenomena that is related to national defense concerns.

99
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:17,000
In Brazil alone, there are hundreds of episodes, but three at least were closely overseen by the armed forces and the Brazilian intelligence and defense systems.

100
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:34,000
One occurred in the state of Pará, in the 70s, another one was in the 80s, in a town called São José dos Campos, and the other one was in the 90s, in the south of Minas Gerais, in the town of Varginha.

101
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:46,000
These episodes were documented, were overseen, the armed forces were interested in the subject, because there was a concern that these events could pose a risk to national defense and security.

102
00:09:46,000 --> 00:10:03,000
And naturally, this, for me, someone who's always been concerned with issues pertaining to national security and national defense, as also part of Brazil's foreign policy.

103
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:09,000
This is what led me to keep up with at least these three events.

104
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Hmm, I'm very excited to talk about all three events.

105
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:18,000
I want to start with Prado, Operation Prado in 1977, Calares.

106
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:30,000
It's a fascinating case, and it's a very dark case, because you have the people in this village, this little fishing village, were being terrorized, essentially.

107
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:35,000
They called it the Chupa Chupa, because their blood was being extracted.

108
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,000
The mayor was in deep fear.

109
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:48,000
You had men and women sleeping in 50 to 60, you know, in one place, just so, you know, the men could defend the women.

110
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:57,000
Because often it was younger females that were the targets of these sorts of attacks, and it felt like lasers and directed energy were being beamed at them.

111
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:06,000
So, what do you know about this, and what do you know about this specifically that the rest of the public might not know?

112
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:14,000
Well, Jesse, what all of us who keep up with this phenomena know is what has been documented, and there's a lot of it.

113
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Because there is testimony of the military who were in charge of the operation, because they had to send a whole task force to monitor these phenomena.

114
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:40,000
And there are accounts of not only military, but also a physician, a doctor, who attended to the victims of these incursions, of these strange, unidentified beings.

115
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:46,000
At night, they would see those objects in flight, and the method never varied.

116
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:54,000
As it was flying, the object would cast down a beam of light, that light illuminated the person and paralyzed them.

117
00:11:54,000 --> 00:12:05,000
From in that white light came a second beam, which was yellowish in color and roughly 30 cm in diameter, that would be pointed at the person's chest.

118
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:09,000
After that, there was another beam that was red.

119
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,000
This beam would make a puncture.

120
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:20,000
It extracted blood and also put something in the body of the victim, something like an implant.

121
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,000
There were several deaths.

122
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:30,000
So there's a suspicion that they were laser beams.

123
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:35,000
But no one really knows what kind of beam struck and affected those people.

124
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:42,000
And after being hit, these people had perforations, blood loss, they were anemic.

125
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
They also suffered other…

126
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:48,000
They felt numbness in their bodies.

127
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:57,000
A number of injuries that were identified by the physician who assisted these people.

128
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:12,000
And the officers who witnessed it and set up the whole operation in this village, in the state of Pará, documented these objects as they were approaching.

129
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,000
And they couldn't identify where they were.

130
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:17,000
So, that has been fully documented.

131
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:23,000
Now, part of the reports and accounts of this event and the operation,

132
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:30,000
I mean, it was a long operation, still remains classified,

133
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:36,000
kept by the armed forces.

134
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:43,000
But that which has been documented is substantial evidence of the existence of the phenomena,

135
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:51,000
of the people that were victims of the contact with these unidentified objects,

136
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:58,000
and accounts by highly credible people.

137
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:04,000
These are officers from the armed forces and the physician who tended to these patients,

138
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:10,000
who had complications and injuries that stemmed from the event that took place in the state of Pará.

139
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:18,000
And you had an official investigation that it sort of prompted.

140
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:21,000
It was, you know, Operation Prado.

141
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:27,000
And you had Captain Holanda Lima go in and investigate.

142
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,000
He brought a whole team.

143
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:31,000
They documented 300 plus encounters.

144
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:37,000
They took 500 photographs and they recorded 15 hours of Super 8 film footage.

145
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:41,000
And they had a whole documentation that was over 2,000 pages.

146
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:47,000
He himself actually saw an alien being that was in a space suit.

147
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:50,000
And the being sort of gave him a hug.

148
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:56,000
And he went on record about this later, about two decades later in 1997.

149
00:14:56,000 --> 00:15:00,000
And then he sadly committed suicide a few months after that.

150
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:03,000
The Super 8 footage.

151
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:08,000
This is still, I believe, exists in the defense ministry.

152
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Did you ever see it?

153
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:12,000
And do you have access to it?

154
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Jesse, there is no question that there was an official operation executed by the Brazilian Armed Forces to monitor this phenomenon.

155
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:26,000
With the title, Operation Prado.

156
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,000
So, this isn't up for debate.

157
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:31,000
The operation took place.

158
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:39,000
It was an official operation led by the Armed Forces to monitor these phenomena in the state of Pará.

159
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:49,000
The second fact is the existence of the diagnosis and the testimony of the physician regarding the victims that were affected by the same phenomena.

160
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:54,000
There is no question about that either.

161
00:15:54,000 --> 00:16:04,000
The only question that still remains is about a report that was not documented or disclosed.

162
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:11,000
On part of the then-captain, who later became a colonel, when he passed, he was a retired colonel.

163
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:17,000
That part of the report, which is still classified, which remains confidential,

164
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:29,000
is what we didn't have a chance to analyze or witness what it's comprised of.

165
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:32,000
So, we only have access to that which has already been disclosed.

166
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:45,000
And it's a full detailed description of the contact, the testimonials, and the testimony of the members of the armed forces that were responsible for leading the operation.

167
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,000
So, there's no doubt about that.

168
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:56,000
Now, you seem like a very thoughtful person who doesn't just take in evidence that's anomalous and not think about it a lot.

169
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Do you have any leading theories about what Kolaris was?

170
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:04,000
Because it's such a bizarre fact pattern.

171
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:07,000
You had puncture wounds, blood taken.

172
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:11,000
It almost looked like ultraviolet burns on a lot of people.

173
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:23,000
You had a physician who was present, actually, Dr. Carvalho, who famously went on record seeing two women who basically had strokes, who died due to these UFO contact events.

174
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:27,000
Do you have any theories as to what caused all of this?

175
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:34,000
There's a list of injuries, and all of this is part of the diagnosis of the medical report.

176
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:40,000
It wasn't just a matter of the strokes or anemia or blood loss.

177
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:57,000
Other consequences, like numbness, and a variety of others, that resulted from the contact of these people with these unidentified objects and beings.

178
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:05,000
You see, I don't have the scientific knowledge.

179
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:09,000
I was not present during the event.

180
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:17,000
In order to develop a theory regarding the origin of whatever it was that was reported.

181
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:26,000
Not only in this event that happened in Kolaris, but the others as well, like in Varginha.

182
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:42,000
And if science itself, with all of its resources, all of its means, can't clarify, I think it would be reckless on my part in trying to develop my own theory on the origin of these phenomena.

183
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:52,000
It really wouldn't be prudent of me to even attempt to provide a diagnostic after decades of efforts from experts and scientists and people who dedicated their whole lives,

184
00:18:52,000 --> 00:19:00,000
like Nick Pope himself, who went to his grave saying, well, I can't account for the 8% of the facts.

185
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:04,000
Who am I to say anything?

186
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,000
Fair enough.

187
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:11,000
You know, Jacques Bellet is one of the godfathers of UFO research.

188
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,000
He's French.

189
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,000
He's an astronomer.

190
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:16,000
He was actually involved in the invention of the internet.

191
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:21,000
And he came down to Kolaris to investigate.

192
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:26,000
His diaries are called Forbidden Science.

193
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:37,000
And he came to the conclusion because he spoke to Dr. Carvalho, who saw 35 patients who all had the same sunburns and puncture wounds and the two women that died of a stroke.

194
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:42,000
And he was just astonished that science can't even look at it.

195
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:49,000
It's almost too much for humans to cope with, for our kind of epistemology to kind of understand.

196
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:54,000
And so I think that's very fair to not come to a conclusion.

197
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:58,000
But I hope that we can study this in a more official capacity.

198
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,000
You obviously are running for president.

199
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:05,000
There are rumors about conversations between you and Bolsonaro.

200
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:09,000
I know you've had some issues with the Christian Democracy Party.

201
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:17,000
If you were in office, would you start to have that conversation in a more official capacity?

202
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Would you try to get the best and brightest Brazilian scientists on these sorts of topics?

203
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Yes, provided that the common denominator is the national interest.

204
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:35,000
The reserves have to protect national security.

205
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:42,000
I believe that here we have a classic liberal common notion that the state should not have secrets.

206
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:46,000
People can have their secrets. Companies can have their secrets.

207
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:52,000
But there are some people who believe that the state should never hold secrets.

208
00:20:52,000 --> 00:21:07,000
I think there are secrets that are personal, secrets that relate to trade, corporative secrets, scientific secrets, technological secrets,

209
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:11,000
and secrets that are national, of the public interest, that pertain to the state.

210
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:18,000
The state, many times, is forced to adopt procedures that it can't announce publicly,

211
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:25,000
especially in the areas of defense, foreign policy, and intelligence.

212
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:35,000
This information will be revealed taking into account that there is a common agreement with other countries.

213
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:45,000
That's why I conditioned the disclosure of this information from Brazil to the disclosure of the same information from the United States.

214
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:50,000
Because a significant part of this information, and I guarantee you, is shared.

215
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:57,000
If a man who is an expert migrated from the UK to the United States to do the same job,

216
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:04,000
it's because there was some level of reciprocity, or you could even call it complicity,

217
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:10,000
between the intelligence services of both countries, with regards to sharing this information.

218
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:23,000
So, to the extent that this information may be shared and disclosed under a reciprocal agreement,

219
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:29,000
this should be done for the benefit of science, for the dissemination of knowledge,

220
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:38,000
even if it does eventually, in many cases, raise a sense of uncertainty and suspicion.

221
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:44,000
Because, of course, if you admit that there is life outside of our planet, it's not a small matter.

222
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:51,000
It isn't merely scientific, it involves morals, it involves philosophy, and religion.

223
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:55,000
Some very sensitive nerves are going to be touched upon,

224
00:22:55,000 --> 00:23:00,000
that have to do with human history, human culture, and human traditions.

225
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:07,000
So, it's very important to be cautious when you touch on these very delicate, sensitive issues,

226
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:11,000
that have to do with the values of humanity, which is a must.

227
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:17,000
Brazil is very interesting to touch on what you just said,

228
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:22,000
because it sits at the intersection between traditional Catholicism,

229
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:26,000
but you have people practicing traditional Catholicism,

230
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:33,000
and also Candomblé, Umbanda, Alan Kardich is a, you know, spiritist from the 1850s,

231
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:38,000
who obviously had his whole taxonomy of, you know, non-corporeal beings,

232
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,000
you know, huge following in Brazil.

233
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:46,000
And so, it's an interesting place in that you have the traditional religious element,

234
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:50,000
but you also have the openness to some of these phenomena.

235
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:56,000
And so, do you think, UFOs, in your mind, do you think it's consistent with Catholicism?

236
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:59,000
How do you think people in Brazil would react?

237
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:04,000
Because, in my experience, I almost think that it feels more natural,

238
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:10,000
and it feels like they're more open to the phenomena than in places even like the U.S.

239
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:18,000
Jesse, the concern regarding this subject appears in a very indirect way.

240
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:22,000
When I was really young, there was a book that was released here.

241
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:25,000
It was super successful. Everyone read it.

242
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:31,000
Chariots of the Gods, the Portuguese title would translate to

243
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:33,000
Were the Gods Astronauts?

244
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:36,000
So, did they build the pyramids?

245
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:39,000
And that ignited a wave of curiosity.

246
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:43,000
Science fiction movies, movies about extraterrestrials,

247
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:48,000
the possibility, or not, of the existence of extraterrestrial life.

248
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:53,000
All of this raises a huge commotion, a lot of curiosity,

249
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:57,000
especially when fiction addresses these ideas.

250
00:24:57,000 --> 00:25:01,000
So, it shows that people have a lot of interest and curiosity about the subject.

251
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:05,000
And maybe even beyond interest and curiosity,

252
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:11,000
it also reflects and reveals an existential concern.

253
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:14,000
In other words, what are we in the world?

254
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:16,000
Are we alone?

255
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:19,000
What if we're not alone?

256
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:24,000
How do you explain these other forms of life, these other beings?

257
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:32,000
If we, here, were created in the image and likeness of God,

258
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:35,000
if this was how man was created,

259
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:41,000
are we ready for a different circumstance, another hypothesis?

260
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:48,000
I believe that this has to be discussed with a lot of respect and a lot of caution.

261
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:52,000
It's not something that can be subject of mere speculation.

262
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:56,000
Unless we're talking about fiction, then it's absolutely fine.

263
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:59,000
Movies, literature, talking about if Gods were astronauts,

264
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:03,000
about an alien aboard a spaceship, that's fiction.

265
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:09,000
Science, however, has another level of responsibility.

266
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:11,000
It can't treat the subject that way.

267
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:14,000
There's a book by Carl Sagan,

268
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:18,000
who was probably one of the greatest scientific exponents in the United States,

269
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:21,000
called Demon Haunted World,

270
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:28,000
in which he touches upon the amount of scientific ignorance of American society,

271
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:31,000
of rulers, of statesmen.

272
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:37,000
Ronald Reagan, for example, would rely on a card reader to make his decisions.

273
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:42,000
Back then he would say that there was only one that had a background in science,

274
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:46,000
which was the Prime Minister of the UK, who had a degree in chemistry.

275
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:50,000
So he would say that the average American was so ignorant, scientifically speaking,

276
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:54,000
that they had the equivalent mentality of someone from the end of the 19th century.

277
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:59,000
So these people would look at science from a great, great distance.

278
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,000
Their worldview is explained by the presence of demons,

279
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:06,000
and not by the presence of science.

280
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:08,000
So that has to be taken into account.

281
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,000
That situation.

282
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:14,000
According to him, a survey was done with Americans,

283
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:20,000
asking them how they believed the dinosaurs had vanished.

284
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:22,000
And 90% of Americans would say,

285
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:25,000
well, it's because they couldn't fit into Noah's Ark.

286
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,000
And that's why they disappeared,

287
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:31,000
because they were left out of Noah's Ark.

288
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:34,000
So this issue has to be taken into account.

289
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:37,000
And it's not exclusive to the US, it's all over the world.

290
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:42,000
It's true.

291
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:47,000
And that's a great book by Carl Sagan, The Demon Haunted World.

292
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:51,000
Sagan's very interesting, though, because he also wrote the movie Contact,

293
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:54,000
and the book, Pale Blue Dot.

294
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:58,000
And in his early diaries as a child, he speculates a lot about UFOs.

295
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:02,000
He has clearly a wonder for, you know, the universe.

296
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:06,000
And he talks about, you know, platonic objects, you know,

297
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:11,000
things like higher dimensional space objects that, you know,

298
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:14,000
like a tesseract that you would only see the shadow of

299
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:16,000
if you were kind of on a lower plane.

300
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:19,000
And so, you know, I go back and forth.

301
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:22,000
I wonder what he actually believed about UFOs.

302
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:25,000
And I know Nancy Reagan and probably Ronald Reagan

303
00:28:25,000 --> 00:28:26,000
had their astrologer.

304
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:32,000
But maybe sometimes, you know, mystical ways of knowing

305
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:35,000
are also, you know, valid, too.

306
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:40,000
You know, Baba Vanga would, you know, regularly advise world leaders.

307
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:43,000
I believe Bolsonaro, who you've, you know,

308
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:45,000
now have sort of a friendly relationship with,

309
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:48,000
he, I think, has an astrologer as well.

310
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:51,000
Yes, and there is a type of astrology,

311
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:55,000
which would turn to knowledge as well,

312
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,000
which is Egyptian astrology.

313
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:03,000
It's not the astrology that comes from horoscopes that you read in the newspaper.

314
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:05,000
That's another thing.

315
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:10,000
The astrology that was referred to in Egypt

316
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:16,000
was based on the rigorous examination of the stars.

317
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:25,000
It wasn't this mere poppycock made to sell these packages with astrology and horoscope issues

318
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:27,000
that were sold with daily papers.

319
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:33,000
There's another important book by Carl Sagan, which it's called, I'm not sure in English,

320
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:36,000
but in Brazil it's called Billions and Billions.

321
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:42,000
And he touches upon this issue with a lot of care and a lot of sensibility.

322
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:45,000
And I believe that in this way,

323
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:54,000
I believe that the care taken into how science should approach this subject

324
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:59,000
has to do with taking into account the scientific knowledge of people.

325
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:03,000
Because you shouldn't really breed desperation or create panic.

326
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,000
It's very easy to create panic.

327
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:14,000
You know the Orson Welles story, the radio show.

328
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:20,000
In other words, he created panic by simply telling a story that wasn't real.

329
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:22,000
It was fake news.

330
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:27,000
But since he was such a competent and efficient communicator,

331
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:31,000
as Orson Welles was known for, he whipped up a panic on a news radio show.

332
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:35,000
So I understand the caution and the prudence of science,

333
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:40,000
because it's different from a mere opinion,

334
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:47,000
from a piece of literature, a short story, a novel, a movie.

335
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:51,000
When science makes a statement about a specific subject,

336
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:54,000
there's a weight to it,

337
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:59,000
which is not the same as what fiction authors write about.

338
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,000
Very well said.

339
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,000
I want to go kind of in chronological order.

340
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:11,000
So we talked about Operation Prado, Kolaris in 1977.

341
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:20,000
In 1986, in May, you had 21 unidentified objects spotted in four different Brazilian states.

342
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:26,000
You had six fighter jets that were dispatched from bases near Brasilia and Rio.

343
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:29,000
And all of them were scrambled by these objects.

344
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:34,000
And you have the Air Force making a very fascinating official statement on the whole thing,

345
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:40,000
saying these were basically aircraft flying in ways that we technically don't understand.

346
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:44,000
They were flying, you know, at extreme speeds and maneuverability.

347
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:47,000
What do you know about that night in 1986?

348
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:54,000
Yes, and in fact, the fighters that we had at the time were state of the art.

349
00:31:54,000 --> 00:32:02,000
The F-5 jets, which were American, but also the Mirage fighters that came from a base close to Brasilia,

350
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:09,000
the Annapolis Air Base, which was built very close to the capital of the country.

351
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:14,000
And those jets flew from the base in Santa Cruz, in the state of Rio de Janeiro,

352
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:20,000
and from the Annapolis Air Base in Goiás in the attempt to intercept the UFOs.

353
00:32:20,000 --> 00:32:29,000
But after that, other pilots in the Air Force reported very similar phenomena.

354
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:39,000
And long after that, and in the 80s, there were many reports by pilots from the Air Force that were documented.

355
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:45,000
One of them, for example, was a pilot that was flying from Chile to Brazil, flying a fighter jet.

356
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:52,000
And he says that an object made its approach at a very high speed,

357
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:57,000
and that when he tried to approach it, the object took off, and this is documented,

358
00:32:57,000 --> 00:33:04,000
at a speed of 25,000 kilometers an hour, according to what the radar picked up.

359
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:11,000
So the existence of the phenomena is undisputed.

360
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:18,000
I sat down with José Manuel Fernández, who worked for the Brazilian Air Force for 34 years,

361
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:25,000
and was an air traffic controller at Sao Paulo's Congonhas Airport on May 19, 1986.

362
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:34,000
This was the same night as the mass sighting known as Brazil's Night of UFOs.

363
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:40,000
Fernández watched in real time as fighter jets scrambled to intercept these UFOs,

364
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:44,000
only to be completely outmaneuvered and outmatched.

365
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:47,000
So I relayed the information.

366
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:54,000
I could see the fighter jet, the F-5 fighter jet.

367
00:33:54,000 --> 00:34:01,000
You know, reach supersonic speed to try and reach the object.

368
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:10,000
But curiously enough, and I can assure you, that I speak the truth.

369
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:16,000
Even though the F-5 was moving at supersonic speed,

370
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:21,000
as the fighter jet was in pursuit of the object,

371
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:26,000
I could even see the tracks that were left by the fighter jet.

372
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:31,000
You know, the object was just playing hide and seek.

373
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:35,000
It would just show up and appear at a very distant point.

374
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
So when the F-5 would try to come closer,

375
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:41,000
the object would just simply disappear,

376
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:45,000
and then just reappear further down.

377
00:34:56,000 --> 00:35:03,000
What's up for debate is what these phenomena are.

378
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:09,000
That's what still has to be investigated, discussed, identified.

379
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:17,000
And this could also be an effort that is more in the interest of science

380
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:19,000
than the interest of defense.

381
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:25,000
Because really, when it comes to the national defense of countries,

382
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:29,000
this was never reported as a risk or threat, right?

383
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:31,000
Or registered as such.

384
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:36,000
The information that these objects would be trying to collect or capture

385
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:41,000
really cannot be verified.

386
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:48,000
However, in terms of threats or risks or even damage for the defense of Brazil,

387
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:51,000
the United States, England, Russia,

388
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:56,000
there's no record that any of these phenomena resulted in damage for these countries.

389
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:59,000
So therefore, from the point of view of national defense,

390
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:03,000
it's a permanent reason of concern, but it's not really a risk.

391
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:08,000
So much so that the concerns in Brazil in the area of defense have subsided.

392
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:14,000
But what still remains is the question, the shadowy area,

393
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:18,000
what hasn't been brought to light in terms of science.

394
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:20,000
To this day, from a scientific point of view,

395
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:25,000
there's more dark than light when it comes to these phenomena.

396
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:33,000
You've mentioned some of these UFO cases in the context of advanced technology.

397
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Do you think that some of what we've experienced maybe on this night, for example, in 1986,

398
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:47,000
or some of these other Brazilian encounters are not in fact, you know, other beings,

399
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:49,000
but they're our own advanced technology.

400
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:53,000
Obviously, the United States has conducted military, you know,

401
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:56,000
secret operations in Brazil since World War II.

402
00:36:56,000 --> 00:37:07,000
Jesse, it's very hard to believe that the United States commands the technology to produce objects

403
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:11,000
that can move at 25,000 kilometers an hour.

404
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:22,000
The U.S. sacrificed a generation of their best pilots in trying to overtake the Russians during the space race.

405
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:31,000
When Gagarin, Yuri Gagarin, took his first orbit trip and the world was astonished,

406
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:35,000
the U.S. entered a situation of despair and panic

407
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:41,000
because they were surpassed in an event that gave the Soviet Union international projection.

408
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:49,000
Gagarin was received in New York and São Paulo as a celebrity, respected, cherished and admired around the world.

409
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:54,000
To overcome this, an American author wrote a novel about this.

410
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,000
They actually made a movie about it as well.

411
00:37:56,000 --> 00:38:01,000
They brought together the best pilots in America to an air base.

412
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:06,000
And the majority of them died trying to do it because they didn't have the equipment.

413
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,000
They didn't have the material.

414
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:12,000
It couldn't resist a space flight.

415
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:21,000
And the widows learned of the deaths of their husbands, of these very young pilots because they didn't have the right material.

416
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:31,000
If the U.S. in fact had the material that would resist what was seen involving these objects,

417
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:35,000
they wouldn't have sacrificed their own pilots.

418
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:41,000
I'm not sure if it was Paul Kennedy, a writer, who described this in a very nice novel about…

419
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:44,000
No, it was the same one who wrote A Bonfire of the Vanities.

420
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:46,000
This one that wrote a book.

421
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:49,000
Tom Wolfe wrote the right stuff.

422
00:38:49,000 --> 00:39:01,000
Tom Wolfe wrote the novel about the sacrifice of these young pilots for America in the space race.

423
00:39:01,000 --> 00:39:08,000
So I don't think that it had anything to do with espionage on part of the U.S. or even the Russians.

424
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:17,000
They didn't have that material available with that degree of resistance that would endure that kind of speed.

425
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:20,000
It would have melted by much slower speed than that.

426
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:27,000
So that kind of explanation just isn't reasonable.

427
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:29,000
Yeah.

428
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:34,000
I mean, even in the 80s, the U.S. was just starting to build stealth craft.

429
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:44,000
But the rumor, even the rumors of the most advanced stealth craft was Mach 4, Mach 5, which is, you know, 3,000 to 4,000 miles per hour.

430
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:50,000
So 25,000 is just orders of magnitude more advanced than, you know, anything that we had.

431
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:53,000
Maybe you had some unmanned drone there, but I don't know.

432
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:55,000
I think it's very hard to believe.

433
00:39:55,000 --> 00:40:07,000
So you would agree with the Air Force Minister Brigadier Octavio Julio Morea Lima's statement that these things, we detected them, they were what they were, and that the facts are what they are.

434
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:09,000
And we don't know what they are.

435
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:11,000
You would agree with that, that these are sort of genuine?

436
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:12,000
I agree.

437
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:13,000
Absolutely.

438
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,000
Totally.

439
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:15,000
We…

440
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:19,000
We don't know what they are, what these phenomena are.

441
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:21,000
We don't know what these objects are.

